 BY FOLASHADE KEHINDE ROSEMARY Adebutu, wife of Chairman of Premier Lotto, Chief Kessington Adebutu, popularly called Baba Ijebu, is dead. Unconfirmed reports linked her death to COVID-19 complications. She was said to have died on Saturday morning. The deceased was the mother of Temitope Adebutu, ex-wife of Jonwo, one of the sons of former President Olusegun Obasanjo. She was said to have been rushed to St. Nicholas Hospital after she developed a mild ailment which later became severe. She was reportedly confirmed: “Brought in Dead” at the hospital. The family had yet to issue an official statement as of the time filing this report. The news was however broken by Street Journal.  